Mattise Directory Layout

+ Root
	- src
		- arch
			- x86
				- x64
			- arm
				- armv7
		- mach
			- pc
			- omap3
		- include
	- doc
	- build

The root directory contains the Makefile for the project as well as assorted
files related to the source code (eg, README, LICENSE).

The 'arch' directory contains architecture-specific code, such as memory
management implementations and startup code. This is all CPU support code.

The 'mach' directory contains machine-specific code, such as hardware
enumeration, startup code, and machine-specific device drivers.

The 'build' directory contains object files and disk images generated by the
build.

The 'include' directory contains header files for use across the project.
